text.tspan: The monthly total number of reported cases of H5N1, a type of highly-pathogenic avian influenza, among
humans. Only a fraction of potential cases of influenza are tested by labs to confirm whether they have influenza
and to identify their strain. The level of testing may vary between countries and over time.
Data source: WHO, Global Influenza Programme (2023)
